    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1962-05-03T17:03:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1962-05-03T17:03:00-05:00" n="182"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d182">
                <head>182. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Vietnam</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d182fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 751K.5811/4-2862. Secret. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_CSJ3"
                            >Cottrell</persName>, and cleared with Loftus, <persName
                            corresp="#p_HWA2">Harriman</persName>, and <persName corresp="#p_REE1"
                            >Rice</persName>. Also sent to Seoul and repeated to <gloss
                            target="#t_CINCPAC1">CINCPAC</gloss> for <gloss target="#t_Polad1"
                            >Polad</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1962-05-03T18:03:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 3, 1962—6:03 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1281. Task Force Viet-Nam.</p>
                <pb facs="0395" n="375" xml:id="pg_375"/>
                <p>Seoulʼs 1135 to Department.<note n="2" xml:id="d182fn2">See <ref
                            target="#d181fn2">footnote 2, Document 181</ref>.</note> Unless Task
                    Force/Saigon, <gloss target="#t_CINCPAC1">CINCPAC</gloss> or Embassy Seoul has
                    other view we believe a quiet covert Korean military experts survey mission to
                    Viet-Nam outlined <gloss target="#t_reftel1">reftel</gloss> should not be
                    discouraged.</p>
                <p>Request Embassy Seoul inform Koreans we appreciate fact their experience may be
                    useful in Viet-Nam and would like to have them work closely with <gloss
                        target="#t_MACV1">MACV</gloss> informing it fully of recommendations they
                    may formulate as result their survey. ROK ideas on intelligence management
                    materiel and anti-aircraft might conceivably cross lines with <gloss
                        target="#t_MACV1">MACV</gloss> thinking so full discussion and clarification
                    between <gloss target="#t_MACV1">MACV</gloss> and ROK would be desirable prior
                    to ROK submission any report to <gloss target="#t_GVN1">GVN</gloss>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BGW1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Ball</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
